NOTE — DESIGN.md said companion thread calls proc.stdout.close() to force reader EOF. On macOS, closing the read-end of a pipe does not reliably interrupt a blocking read() in another thread (POSIX undefined). Primary mechanism changed to select-based poll with 1 s timeout in _read_loop; companion thread kept as belt-and-suspenders.
NOTE — DESIGN.md said _on_runner_done uses QTimer.singleShot(0,…) to marshal done state to main thread. QTimer.singleShot from a non-GUI daemon thread is unreliable in PyQt6; replaced with bridge.state_changed.emit(state) (Qt queued-connection, thread-safe). _handle_done method removed.
